         'flash <a href="/wiki/Memory_chip" class="mw-redirect" title="Memory '
         'chip">memory chip</a>, with 2<span class="nowrap">\xa0'
         '</span>trillion <a href="/wiki/Floating-gate_MOSFET" '
         'title="Floating-gate MOSFET">floating-gate MOSFETs</a> (<a '
         'href="/wiki/Multi-level_cell" title="Multi-level cell">4<span '
         'class="nowrap">\xa0</span>bits per transistor</a>).<sup '
         'id="cite_ref-electronicsweekly-samsung_9-0" class="reference"><a '
         'href="#cite_note-electronicsweekly-samsung-9">[9]</a></sup> As of '
         '2020<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" '
         'style="display:none;"><a class="external text" '
         'href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Transistor_count&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>, '
         'the highest transistor count in any IC chip is a <a '
         'href="/wiki/Deep_learning" title="Deep learning">deep learning</a> '
         'engine called the Wafer Scale Engine 2 by Cerebras, using a special '
         'design to route around any non-functional core on the device; it has '
         '2.6<span class="nowrap">\xa0</span>trillion MOSFETs, manufactured '
         'using TSMC\'s <span class="nowrap">7\xa0nm</span> FinFET '
         'process.<sup id="cite_ref-ExtremeTech-WSE_10-0" class="reference"><a '
         'href="#cite_note-ExtremeTech-WSE-10">[10]</a></sup><sup '
         'id="cite_ref-NextPlatform-WSE_11-0" class="reference"><a '
         'href="#cite_note-NextPlatform-WSE-11">[11]</a></sup><sup '
         'id="cite_ref-AnandTech-WSE_12-0" class="reference"><a '
