 'text': '<p><i><b>Trends</b></i> is a series of <a '
         'href="/wiki/Scientific_journal" title="Scientific '
         'journal">scientific journals</a> owned by <a href="/wiki/Elsevier" '
         'title="Elsevier">Elsevier</a> that publish <a '
         'href="/wiki/Review_journal" class="mw-redirect" title="Review '
         'journal">review articles</a> in a range of areas of <a '
         'href="/wiki/Biology" title="Biology">biology</a> and <a '
         'href="/wiki/Chemistry" title="Chemistry">chemistry</a>. They are '
         'currently part of Elsevier\'s <a href="/wiki/Cell_Press" title="Cell '
         'Press">Cell Press</a> group of journals.\n'
         '</p><p>The <i>Trends</i> series was founded in 1976 with <i>Trends '
         'in Biochemical Sciences</i> (TIBS), rapidly followed by <i>Trends in '
         'Neurosciences</i> (TINS), <i>Trends in Pharmacological Sciences</i> '
         '(TIPS) and <i>Immunology Today</i>. \n'
         '</p><p><i>Immunology Today</i>, <i>Parasitology Today</i> and '
         '<i>Molecular Medicine Today</i> changed their names to <i>Trends '
         'in...</i> in 2001. <i><a href="/wiki/Drug_Discovery_Today" '
         'title="Drug Discovery Today">Drug Discovery Today</a></i> was spun '
         'off as an independent brand.\n'
